FT  10 JUL 93 / UK Company News: British Bloodstock loss cut to Pounds
38,000
British Bloodstock Agency cut its loss from Pounds 55,000 to Pounds 38,000
in the year to end-March.
The trading improvement, however, was Pounds 370,000 as the previous year
took in Pounds 353,000 profit on property disposal. It had been achieved
notwithstanding continued policy of prudent provision for doubtful debts and
a further writing down of stallion shares.
Costs had been cut by Pounds 1m since 1990 and further savings would be
sought to assist a return to profitability and dividends as soon as
possible. Losses per share were 1.4p, against 3p.
